@startuml fork-workflow
title The fork workflow has a hole when refs/dolt/data carries the payload

skinparam monochrome false
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
    BorderColor #666
    RoundCorner 8
}

cloud "UPSTREAM\nidvorkin/dolt-thing" as UP #E6F4EA {
    rectangle "refs/heads/main\n(README — seed)" as UP_H #D9EDFF
    rectangle "refs/dolt/data\n(STALE after AI push)" as UP_D #F5C2C7
}

cloud "FORK\nidvorkin-ai-tools/dolt-thing" as FK #FFF8D6 {
    rectangle "refs/heads/main\n(README — same seed)" as FK_H #D9EDFF
    rectangle "refs/dolt/data\n(has AI's new row)" as FK_D #C4E2AC
}

node "AI-tools dev box\n(fork write only)" as DEV #EAF3FF
node "Igor\n(upstream write)" as ADMIN #EAF3FF

DEV -[#0969DA]-> FK_D : dolt push origin main\nadvances refs/dolt/data
DEV -[#999,dashed]-> FK_H : refs/heads/main unchanged\n(dolt doesn't touch it)

UP_H -[hidden]- FK_H
UP_D -[hidden]- FK_D

note bottom of FK
  PR fork->upstream compares
  refs/heads/main on both sides.
  Both are the seed commit.
  **GitHub diff view is empty.**
  Merge button advances nothing
  useful — refs/dolt/data stays
  stale on upstream.
end note

ADMIN -[#C0A02E]-> UP_D : dolt fetch fork\n+ dolt merge fork/main\n+ dolt push upstream main
note right of ADMIN
  Only path that actually
  moves the data to upstream.
  Requires upstream write —
  AI-tools does not have it.
end note

@enduml
